strings.Value: [Jokingly punch Amiri on the shoulder] "So, warrior, are you ready to beat the hell out of the Eldest and his minions?"
"Do you want to tell me anything before we set off for battle?"
"All right, enough talk. I know you don't like it."

{n}Amiri ruffles her dark hair with her hand.{/n} "Ha... We were just getting ready for our last great battle — and now we're doing it again! It's a good thing I decided to follow you back there at Aldori's. You definitely know how to have fun, chief!"

"I do! You're a good chief, and our tribe is all right, and we've been through a lot of good fights! Don't think I'm sucking up or something... it's just that I live like I want now. And that makes me sing inside!"

{n}The barbarian grins, then returns the friendly jab.{/n} "Oh no, I'm not ready! Wait, I need to polish my sword — and tie some ribbons to my belt! Then I'll be ready for battle!" {n}Amiri laughs, pleased with her joke.{/n}
"Right! Go on, chief, give the order!"
